title: Bluegrass Student Union - Legacy
description: Bluegrass Student Union is the Louisville, Kentucky barbershop quartet who won the 1978 SPEBSQSA International competition. They distinguished themselves by performing at a high level of proficiency on stage and in the recording studio throughout their 33-year career, by becoming the youngest quartet to win the SPEBSQSA championship, and by continually improving their art, even after winning their gold medals
